sql:
SELECT trip_date, trip_duration, distance, purpose
FROM work_trips
WHERE trip_duration > 30;

SELECT mode_id, SUM(mode_frequency) AS total_frequency
FROM trip_modes
GROUP BY mode_id;

SELECT purpose, SUM(distance) AS total_distance, AVG(carpool_size) AS average_carpool_size
FROM work_trips
GROUP BY purpose;

external_knowledge:
The purpose of a work trip is typically for commuting to and from a workplace or traveling as part of one's occupation; 
the total distance traveled is calculated by summing the distances of individual work trips; 
age groups, income brackets, and genders are used to categorize the population for demographic analysis.

